1. First init git in pj folder.
> git init

2. create a repository in gitHub

In the pj folder , open terminal and run
3. > git remote add origin copyHttpName

4. > git push -u origin main 

//adding files to git repo
    - git status (to check new added file and conditions)
    - git add index.html/. (add to staging area)
    - git commit -m "added" (add to version control - local repo)
    - git push -u origin main (push local repo to remote repo)

// other commands
- ls -Hidden (check hidden git file)
- git log (to check which commit has done)
- git rm --cached -r . (remove every files from staging area) . means all
- git clone httpLink (cloning git repo)

// branch
git branch name (create)
git branch (check all branches)
git checkout name (switch branch)
git merge branchName  (merge branch)
